ObjectStates.LuaScript:
tagZoneGUID = '0f7a92'


function onDropped()
	local zone = getObjectFromGUID(tagZoneGUID)
	if zone != nil then
		local params = self.getPosition()
		zone.setPosition(params)
	else
		print('no zone found, check zone and guid')
	end
end

function onObjectEnterScriptingZone(zone, object)
	if zone.getGUID() == tagZoneGUID then
		local nm = self.getName()
		local descr = self.getDescription()
		if nm != nil and nm != '' and nm != 'null' then
			object.setName(nm)
		end
		if descr != nil and descr != '' and descr != 'null' then
			object.setDescription(descr)
		end
	end
end

ObjectStates.Name: Notecard
ObjectStates.Description:
1) Set the desired name or description to be applied to the objects by setting the name/description field of the tagging zone.

Leave blank or write "null" in a field for that field to not be used.

2) Swipe or drop object into tagging area.  It should gain the name and/or description.

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Token
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
inputGUID = 'a68ac0'
outputGUID = '817ec7'
deckToDo = {}
backupName = ''
backupDescr = ''

function onCollisionEnter(collision_info)
	local object = collision_info.collision_object
	if object.tag == 'Deck' then
		if object != deckToDo then
			deckToDo = object
			backupName = object.getName()
			backupDescr = object.getDescription()
			local params = {backupName, backupDescr}
			getObjectFromGUID(outputGUID).call('loadBackup', params)
			startLuaCoroutine(self, 'doThings' )
		end
	elseif object.tag == 'Card' then
		dontLeaveMe(object)
	end
end

function doThings()
	local deck = deckToDo
	if deck then
		print('wait for it!')
		local nm = self.getName()
		local descr = self.getDescription()
		local card = {}
		local params = {}
		params.position = getObjectFromGUID(outputGUID).getPosition()
		local count = deck.getQuantity()
		local max = count - 1
		for i = 1, max do
			params.position.y = params.position.y + 1
			card = deck.takeObject(params)
			for t=1, 5 do
				coroutine.yield(0)
			end
			if nm != nil and nm != '' and nm != 'null' then
				card.setName(nm)
			end
			if descr != nil and descr != '' and descr != 'null' then
				card.setDescription(descr)
			end
		end
	end
	for i= 1, 120 do
		coroutine.yield(0)
	end
	return 1
end

function dontLeaveMe(card)
	if card then
		print("last card: don't leave me behind!")
		local nm = self.getName()
		local descr = self.getDescription()
		local params = {}
		params.position = getObjectFromGUID(outputGUID).getPosition()
		params.position.y = params.position.y + 100
		if nm != nil and nm != '' and nm != 'null' then
			card.setName(nm)
		end
		if descr != nil and descr != '' and descr != 'null' then
			card.setDescription(descr)
		end
		card.setPosition(params.position)
	end
end

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Token
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
backupName = ''
backupDescr = ''

function onCollisionEnter(collision_info)
	local object = collision_info.collision_object
	if object.tag == 'Deck' then
		local nm = self.getName()
		local descr = self.getDescription()
		if nm != '' and nm != nil and nm != null then
			object.setName(nm)
		elseif backupName != '' and backupName != nil then
			object.setName(backupName)
		end
		if descr != '' and descr != nil and descr != null then
			object.setDescription(descr)
		elseif backupDescr != '' and backupDescr != nil then
			object.setDescription(backupDescr)
		end
	end
end

function loadBackup(params)
	backupName = params[1]
	backupDescr = params[2]
end
